    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1" type="to"
                            >Stalin</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d503fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room, via military
                        channels, and forwarded by the Map Room to Moscow in paraphrase, via Navy
                        channels. The source text is the message as received at the Map Room. The
                        original, in <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">Marshall</persName>’s handwriting
                        and with <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>’s signature, was
                        later sent to <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> and is
                        reproduced in his <hi rend="italic">Crusade in Europe</hi> (New York:
                        Doubleday and Co., 1948), p. 208. It reads “command of <gloss
                            target="#t_Overlord1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                        </gloss> operation” where this text reads “the Command of <gloss
                            target="#t_Overlord1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                        </gloss>”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-06">6 December
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and secret from the President to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_SIV1"
                        >Stalin</persName>.</p>
                <p>The immediate appointment of General <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> to the Command of <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss> has been decided upon.<note n="2" xml:id="d503fn2">See <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_542">p. 542</ref>. For
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>’s acknowledgment, dated
                        December 10, 1943, see <hi rend="italic">
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>’s Correspondence</hi>,
                        vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 114.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
